Hi Wihanga,
I hope this email finds you well. I am reaching out to discuss an important
aspect regarding System X that requires your attention.

As we prepare for the launch of new products, it has come to our attention
that System X currently lacks a dedicated performance test environment.
Given the criticality of assessing the application's performance under
varying loads and conditions, it is imperative that we establish a robust
testing environment to ensure optimal functionality and user experience.

Without a dedicated performance test environment, we run the risk of
encountering unforeseen performance issues and potential disruptions once
the new products are launched. To mitigate this risk and ensure a seamless
rollout, we need to prioritize the establishment of a comprehensive
performance testing infrastructure.

By setting up a dedicated performance test environment, we can:

   1. Evaluate the application's performance under simulated real-world
   conditions.
   2. Identify and address any performance bottlenecks or scalability
   issues proactively.
   3. Ensure that System X can handle the anticipated user load without
   compromising on performance or stability.
   4. Provide stakeholders with confidence in the application's reliability
   and scalability.

I propose that we initiate discussions to outline the requirements and
timelines for setting up the performance test environment for System X.
This will involve collaboration between our teams to define the necessary
infrastructure, tools, and testing scenarios to accurately assess the
application's performance.

I would greatly appreciate your support and involvement in this initiative
to ensure the successful launch of the new products with confidence in
System X's performance capabilities.

Please let me know a convenient time for us to discuss this further, or if
you have any initial thoughts or concerns regarding this matter.

Looking forward to your feedback and collaboration.

Best regards,
Wihanga Anupama

